{
  "texts": [
    "Its elements are called lattice points in R z 1,...,z k i 0,i 1,...,i k-1.We remark that the dependence of the entire construction, as well as the notion of admissibility on the parameters K and M is supressed in our notation.",
    "The quantities K and M will be chosen at the end of the argument.If one were to translate and rescale the rectangle R z 1,...,z k i 0,i 1,...,i k-1 to the rectangle R 0, say via a map f: R d → R d, then the lattice of the rectangle R 0 is the image of the lattice of the rectangle R z 1,...,z k i 0,i 1,...,i k-1.",
    "In particular, each such lattice is merely a rescaled and translated version of the lattice 1K Ref ∪ ( 1 K Ref + 1 K) ∪ • • • ∪ ( 1 K Ref + K -1 K).Thus, each such lattice partitions into K lattices, which are merely rescaled and translated copies of the reference lattice Ref itself.",
    "We recommend consulting also Figure 4.",
    "Note that since each admissible rectangle is a merely a translation of a kind of rectangle that appears as the domain of h in Lemma 5.8, we may apply the lemma to each of these rectangles (of course, we need K and M to be large enough so that the lemma may be applied)."
  ]
}